text: Asnohuañusja (possibly from Quechua asnu donkey (from Spanish asno), wañuy die, -sqa a suffix (wañusqa died, dead)) is a mountain in the western part of the Chila mountain range in the Andes of Peru. It lies in the Arequipa Region, Castilla Province, Chachas District. It is situated southwest of Chila and Choquepirhua, and northwest of Yuraccacsa.escale.minedu.gob.pe - UGEL map of the Caylloma Province 1 (Arequipa Region) == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Arequipa Region
